      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The allure of the Christmas tree in my nonreligious but culturally Jewish house was as strong to my siblings and me growing up as it was to Yona Zeldis McDonough (Soapbox, ''Clashing Symbol,'' Dec. 19).</p>
        <p>Though my parents indulged us, my father saved face by calling it a Hanukkah bush, crowning it with the Star of David instead of the Star of  Bethlehem, and steadfastly maintaining that Dec. 25 was, in fact, the  commemoration of Jesus Christ's bar mitzvah.</p>
        <p>READA BUNIN EDELSTEIN  Upper West Side</p>
      </block>
